## Implementation Plan: Auto-redirect issue short IDs in event view

### Problem
Users typing `sentry event view BRUNCHIE-APP-29` (an issue short ID) get
ResolutionError because the CLI interprets it as a hex event ID. Observed
in Sentry issues CLI-JR, CLI-J6 and 59 similar ResolutionError issues.

### Approach
Two-layer detection:
1. **Proactive** (single-arg): In parsePositionalArgs, when a single arg
   matches looksLikeIssueShortId (uppercase pattern like PROJECT-SUFFIX),
   set issueShortId field to trigger the latest-event fetch path.
2. **Reactive** (two-arg 404): In fetchEventWithContext, when a 404 occurs
   and eventId matches the issue short ID pattern, prepend a suggestion
   to try `sentry issue view` in the error message.

### Key Design Decisions
- Use existing looksLikeIssueShortId (strict uppercase) to avoid false
  positives on project slugs like "my-project"
- Resolve issue via getIssueByShortId then fetch latest event with numeric ID
  (getLatestEvent requires Number(issueId), so short IDs need resolution first)
- Refactored inline issueId handling into resolveIssueShortcut helper to keep
  func() cyclomatic complexity under the limit
- Org resolution for short ID path uses resolveOrg (DSN/env/config cascade)

